    {
      "block_type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "FUNCTION"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "SELF-DIAGNOSIS"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "prose",
      "text": "A self-diagnostic function has been programmed into the ECU. Seven circuits can be checked for possible faults using the N\u00b7CVT warning light to access the problem area.\nConsult can also be used for diagnostics. Refer to the Trouble Diagnosis section for diagnostic procedures.",
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "2. Forward and reverse synchromesh changeover system"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "prose",
      "text": "A synchromesh changeover system allows for forward to reverse shifting, at the same time eliminating \"shift squeak\" (occurs when the belt tries to reverse direction very quickly.)",
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "\"N\" POSITION."
    },
    {
      "block_type": "heading",
      "level": 4,
      "text": "Neutral."
    },
    {
      "block_type": "prose",
      "text": "The synchroniser sleeve is central on the hub, and no power is transmitted.",
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
